Citation.sTitle: Viscosities of Binary Mixtures Containing Isomeric Chlorobutanes and Diisopropylether: Experimental and Predicted Values
Citation.sAbstract: In this work, viscosities of binary mixtures of isomeric chlorobutanes with diisopropylether have been determined as a function of composition under atmospheric pressure and in the temperature range from 283.15 K to 313.15 K with steps of 5 K. Kinematics viscosities were measured using an Ubbelohde viscosimeter; absolute viscosities were obtained from kinematic viscosities and densities. Finally, we have used the Asfour method for predicting the dependence of viscosity with composition and comparing it with our experimental data.
